Package ca.mcgill.ecse211.project

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Display
    This class is used to display the content of the odometer variables (x, y, Theta)
    Launcher
    This controls the launching mechanism.
    LightLocalizer
    Light localization that assumes that the device is facing NORTH and is on a 45 degree line in between (0,0) and (1,1)
    Main  
    Navigation
    Navigates the robot depending on given coordinates avoids obstacles and resumes navigation
    Odometer
    The odometer class keeps track of the robot's (x, y, theta) position.
    Resources
    This class is used to define static resources in one place for easy access and to avoid cluttering the rest of the codebase.
    UltrasonicLocalizer
    Given that the system is placed along an imaginary 45 degree line between (0,0) and (1,1) reorient the system facing NORTH
    UltrasonicPoller
    Simple UltrasonicPoller that samples the US sensor and method returns true when obstacle is detected
